the portfolio’s exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate metrics, and other factors.</p>"}],"esg-stmt-58SCREEN":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<p>ESG integration is the practice of incorporating material environmental, social and governance (ESG) information or insights alongside traditional measures into the investment decision process to improve long term financial outcomes of portfolios. <strong>Unless otherwise stated in Fund documentation or included within the Fund’s investment objective, inclusion of this statement does not imply that the Fund has an ESG-aligned investment objective, but rather describes how ESG information is considered as part of the overall investment process.</strong></p>\n<br />\n<p>The Fund manager designs research, portfolio construction, and decision phases of the investment process to reflect emphasis on relevant, internal ESG research related to assessments of certain characteristics, including, but not limited to, economic and environmental transition, market structure, superior growth, management quality, and risk characteristics associated with environmental, social, and governance matters. ESG insights are combined with other internal research views to achieve active portfolio weighting versus a reference benchmark (or weighting implemented to achieve an absolute return outcome in portfolios without a benchmark) which considers the portfolio’s ESG mandate.  The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio’s exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate metrics, and other factors.</p>"}],"esg-stmt-58THEMATIC":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<p>ESG integration is the practice of incorporating material environmental, social and governance (ESG) information or insights alongside traditional measures into the investment decision process to improve long term financial outcomes of portfolios. <strong>Unless otherwise stated in Fund documentation or included within the Fund’s investment objective, inclusion of this statement does not imply that the Fund has an ESG-aligned investment objective, but rather describes how ESG information is considered as part of the overall investment process.</strong></p>\n<br />\n<p>The Fund manager designs research, portfolio construction, and decision phases of the investment process to reflect emphasis on relevant, internal ESG research related to assessments of certain characteristics, including, but not limited to, economic and environmental transition, market structure, superior growth, management quality, and risk characteristics associated with environmental, social, and governance matters. ESG insights are combined with other internal research views to achieve active portfolio weighting versus a reference benchmark (or weighting implemented to achieve an absolute return outcome in portfolios without a benchmark) which considers the portfolio’s ESG mandate.  The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio’s exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate metrics, and other factors.</p>"}],"esg-stmt-58UPLIFT":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<p>ESG integration is the practice of incorporating material environmental, social and governance (ESG) information or insights alongside traditional measures into the investment decision process to improve long term financial outcomes of portfolios. <strong>Unless otherwise stated in Fund documentation or included within the Fund’s investment objective, inclusion of this statement does not imply that the Fund has an ESG-aligned investment objective, but rather describes how ESG information is considered as part of the overall investment process.</strong></p>\n<br />\n<p>The Fund manager designs research, portfolio construction, and decision phases of the investment process to reflect emphasis on relevant, internal ESG research related to assessments of certain characteristics, including, but not limited to, economic and environmental transition, market structure, superior growth, management quality, and risk characteristics associated with environmental, social, and governance matters. ESG insights are combined with other internal research views to achieve active portfolio weighting versus a reference benchmark (or weighting implemented to achieve an absolute return outcome in portfolios without a benchmark) which considers the portfolio’s ESG mandate.  The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio’s exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate metrics, and other factors.</p>"}],"esg-stmt-60":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-61":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-62":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in the investment research, portfolio construction, and investment monitoring phases of the investment process. The Fund manager maintains internal ESG scorecards for certain issuers under consideration for investment and certain existing issuers of publicly traded securities. These scorecards analyze and track internal and external research views across a range of environmental, social, and governance factors sourced from primary and third-party ESG information and research. Portfolio management teams may consider the sector and issuer ESG views and scores during portfolio construction. The Fund manager also considers ESG criteria during post-investment monitoring and conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock’s Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-63":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in the investment research, portfolio construction, and investment monitoring phases of the investment process. The Fund manager maintains internal ESG scorecards for certain issuers under consideration for investment and certain existing issuers of publicly traded securities. These scorecards analyze and track internal and external research views across a range of environmental, social, and governance factors sourced from primary and third-party ESG information and research. Portfolio management teams may consider the sector and issuer ESG views and scores during portfolio construction. The Fund manager also considers ESG criteria during post-investment monitoring and conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock’s Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-64":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-65":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations throughout the investment process, including sourcing, screening, due diligence, decision, and portfolio monitoring. This may include documented ESG screens preventing the Fund from investing in companies that are engaged in specified excluded sectors. In the due diligence process, the investment team uses an internal ESG risk assessment to identify, analyze and document key ESG risks where appropriate. Where applicable, the Fund manager may also consider third-party ESG data vendors or specialist consultants to support due diligence or company engagement. Potential investments are assigned an ESG rating where appropriate that reflects positive ESG attributes and material ESG risks, if any. Where appropriate, identified ESG risks and relevant mitigating actions may be documented in Investment Committee materials and discussed at relevant Investment Committee meetings. ESG criteria may impact the Investment Committee’s investment decision. The Fund’s ongoing portfolio management process includes, where appropriate, the monitoring of ESG criteria over the life of an investment, and in these cases Fund managers aim to refresh portfolio company ESG ratings on a quarterly basis. Furthermore, the investment team and BlackRock’s Risk and Quantitative Analysis group analyze exposure to material ESG risks where appropriate as part of the portfolio risk review regularly."}],"esg-stmt-67":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-68":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-69":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-70":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-71":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-72":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-73":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-74":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research and due diligence stage of the investment process. The Fund manager has developed internal research signals to help evaluate corporate issuers on climate, governance and human capital issues. ESG information may be sourced from both internal and external sources. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio risk reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-77":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-78":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-79":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-80":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-81":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Where applicable, the Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research and due diligence stage of the investment process. ESG information may be sourced from both internal and external sources and included in the Aladdin risk system. This information may broadly inform investment decisions: ESG criteria are considered in combination with other information. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock's Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-82":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Where applicable, the Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research and due diligence stage of the investment process. ESG information may be sourced from both internal and external sources and included in the Aladdin risk system. This information may broadly inform investment decisions: ESG criteria are considered in combination with other information. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock's Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-83":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Where applicable, the Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research and due diligence stage of the investment process. ESG information may be sourced from both internal and external sources and included in the Aladdin risk system. This information may broadly inform investment decisions: ESG criteria are considered in combination with other information. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock's Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-84":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-87":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information during the investment process. In the initial idea generation and credit research process this may include an assessment of each company's positive ESG attributes or material risks or the use of internal sovereign or corporate ESG due diligence templates alongside third-party ESG data. Positive ESG attributes and material ESG risks and their potential financial impact are generally highlighted in credit research reports and may influence investment decisions and security selection by portfolio managers. From a top-down perspective, ESG aggregate portfolio metrics are available for the Fund manager to review through BlackRock's Aladdin system. The Fund manager also considers environmental, social and governance criteria during post-investment monitoring and conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock’s Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include the analysis and discussion of portfolio exposure to material ESG risks, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-89":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-9":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in the initial screening, sourcing and due diligence phases of the investment process. This may include the use of internal ESG due diligence templates to identify, analyze and document key ESG risks. Specialist consultants may also be appointed to support due diligence. Where appropriate, identified ESG risks are highlighted in Investment Committee materials and discussed at relevant Investment Committee meetings. This information may broadly inform investment decisions: ESG criteria are considered in combination with other information and often with a focus on evaluating asset liquidity and product market fit. The Fund manager also considers environmental, social and governance criteria during post-investment monitoring and conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock’s Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include the analysis and discussion of portfolio exposure to material ESG risks, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-90":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-91":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-92":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in the investment research, portfolio construction, and investment monitoring phases of the investment process. The Fund manager maintains internal ESG scorecards for certain issuers under consideration for investment and certain existing issuers of publicly traded securities. These scorecards analyze and track internal and external research views across a range of environmental, social, and governance factors sourced from primary and third-party ESG information and research. Portfolio management teams may consider the sector and issuer ESG views and scores during portfolio construction. The Fund manager also considers ESG criteria during post-investment monitoring and conducts regular portfolio risk reviews between the investment team and BlackRock’s Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, where appropriate."}],"esg-stmt-93":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-94":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-95":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research phase of the investment process. This may include relevant third-party insights, as well as internal engagement commentary and input from BlackRock Investment Stewardship on governance issues. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group and with the Chief Investment Officers. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-96":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research and due diligence phase of the investment process. ESG information may be sourced internally or from third-party providers. The Fund manager's ongoing monitoring of the portfolio involves regular portfolio risk reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-97":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The Fund manager includes ESG considerations in combination with other information in the research and due diligence stage of the investment process. The Fund manager has developed internal research signals to help evaluate corporate issuers on climate, governance and human capital issues. ESG information may be sourced from both internal and external sources. The Fund manager conducts regular portfolio risk reviews with the Risk and Quantitative Analysis group. These reviews include discussion, where appropriate, of the portfolio's exposure to material ESG risks, as well as exposure to sustainability-related business involvements, climate-related metrics, and other factors."}],"esg-stmt-global":[{"metadata":null,"text":"BlackRock considers many investment risks in our processes. In order to seek the best risk-adjusted returns for our clients, we manage material risks and opportunities that could impact portfolios, including financially material Environmental, Social and/or Governance (ESG) data or information, where available. See our <a href=\"https://www.blackrock.com/corporate/literature/publication/blk-esg-investment-statement-web.pdf\">Firm Wide ESG Integration Statement</a> for more information on this approach and fund documentation for how these material risks are considered within this product, where applicable."}],"exposure-breakdowns.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Allocations are subject to change."}],"exposure-breakdowns.geography.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Geographic exposure relates principally to the domicile of the issuers of the securities held in the product, added together and then expressed as a percentage of the product's total holdings, excluding currency holdings. Percentages do not reflect fair valuation. In some instances, percentages may reflect the location where the issuer of the securities carries out much of their business. Bonds are included in U.S. bond indices when the securities are denominated in U.S. dollars regardless of the domicile of the issuer."}],"exposure-breakdowns.rating.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Ratings are measured on a scale that generally ranges from AAA (S&amp;P highest) or Aaa (Moody's highest) to D (S&amp;P lowest) or C (Moody's lowest). \"R\" applies to securities where the issuing company is under regulatory supervision due to its financial situation. \"SD\" applies to securities where the issuing company has selectively defaulted on some obligations. “NR” applies to securities that are not rated. \"Other\" includes dividends booked but not yet received and, if applicable, short-term fixed income securities.<br />"}],"fee-table.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The amounts shown above are as of the current prospectus, but may not include extraordinary expenses incurred by the Fund over the past fiscal year. Amounts are rounded to the nearest basis point, which in some cases may be \"0.00\"."}],"fee-table.secondary.sub-title":[{"metadata":null,"text":"On Managed Assets"}],"fee-table.sub-title":[{"metadata":null,"text":"as of current prospectus"}],"footer_disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Carefully consider the Fund's investment objectives, risk factors, and charges and expenses before investing. This and other information can be found in the Fund's prospectus, and if available, summary prospectus, which may be obtained by calling 1-800-iShares (1-800-474-2737) or by visiting www.iShares.com or www.blackrock.com. Read the prospectus carefully before investing."},{"metadata":null,"text":"Investing involves risk, including possible loss of principal."},{"metadata":null,"text":"Small-capitalization companies may be less stable and more susceptible to adverse developments, and their securities may be more volatile and less liquid than larger capitalization companies."},{"metadata":null,"text":"Diversification may not protect against market risk or loss of principal. Shares of ETFs are bought and sold at market price (not NAV) and are not individually redeemed from the fund. Any applicable brokerage commissions will reduce returns."},{"metadata":null,"text":"<strong>Index returns are for illustrative purposes only.  Index performance returns do not reflect any management fees, transaction costs or expenses. Indexes are unmanaged and one cannot invest directly in an index. Past performance does not guarantee future results.</strong>"},{"metadata":null,"text":"\"Acquired Fund Fees and Expenses\" reflect the Fund's pro rata share of the indirect fees and expenses incurred by investing in one or more acquired funds, such as mutual funds, business development companies, or other pooled investment vehicles. AFFE are reflected in the prices of the acquired funds and thus included in the total returns of the Fund. <br />The iShares Funds are distributed by BlackRock Investments, LLC (together with its affiliates, \"BlackRock\")."},{"metadata":null,"text":"The Russell Index is a trademark of Russell Investment Group and has been licensed for use by BlackRock. The iShares Funds are not sponsored, endorsed, issued, sold or promoted by Russell Investment Group. Nor does this company make any representation regarding the advisability of investing in the Funds. BlackRock is not affiliated with the company listed above."},{"metadata":null,"text":"BlackRock provides compensation in connection with obtaining or using third-party ratings and rankings.<br />© 2026  BlackRock<span>, Inc. or its affiliates</span>. All rights reserved. <strong>iSHARES</strong>, <strong>iBONDS </strong>and <strong>BLACKROCK</strong> are trademarks of BlackRock, Inc. or its affiliates. <span>All other trademarks are those of their respective owners.</span><span> </span>"},{"metadata":null,"text":"FOR MORE INFORMATION, VISIT WWW.ISHARES.COM OR CALL 1-800 ISHARES (1-800-474-2737)"}],"footer_disclaimer_box":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Not FDIC Insured - No Bank Guarantee - May Lose Value"}],"fund-description":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The iShares Russell 2000 ETF seeks to track the Russell 2000 Index. The fund offers broad exposure to U.S.small-cap stocks."}],"fund-header-hero.documents":[{"metadata":null,"text":"{type=GLS;material=Fact Sheet}"}],"fund-header.disclaimer":[],"fund-header.document_link":[{"metadata":null,"text":"{type=GLS;material=Fact Sheet}{type=GLS;material=Prospectus}"}],"fund-header.documents":[{"metadata":null,"text":"{type=NON-GLS;material=regDocs;url=https://www.blackrock.com/us/individual/resources/regulatory-documents}{type=GLS;material=Product Brief}{type=GLS;material=Fact Sheet}{type=GLS;material=Prospectus}"}],"fund-of-fund.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"If the Fund invests in any underlying fund, certain portfolio information, including sustainability characteristics and business-involvement metrics, provided for the Fund may include information (on a look-through basis) of such underlying fund, to the extent available."}],"fund_objective":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The iShares Russell 2000 ETF seeks to track the investment results of an index composed of small-capitalization U.S. equities."}],"fund_overview.fund_overview":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Performance is not shown as the Fund has a performance history of less than 1 year. You should read the Prospectus and the Key Investor Information Document (KIID) for each fund in which you want to invest."}],"fund_rankings.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Rankings based on total return excluding sales charges, independently calculated and not combined to create an overall ranking. For periods not shown, Morningstar does not provide rankings based on synthetic performance."}],"fund_talking_points":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Exposure to small public U.S. companies"},{"metadata":null,"text":"Access to 2000 small-cap domestic stocks in a single fund"},{"metadata":null,"text":"Use to diversify a U.S. stock allocation and seek long-term growth in your portfolio"}],"fundamentals-and-risk.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"This information must be preceded or accompanied by a current prospectus. For standardized performance, please see the Performance section."}],"glossary":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<strong>Total Expense Ratio (TER):</strong> A measure of the total costs associated with managing and operating a fund. The TER consists primarily of the management fee plus other expenses such as trustee, custody, or operating expenses. It is expressed as a percentage of the fund's total net asset value."},{"metadata":null,"text":"<strong>Distribution yield:</strong> The distribution yield represents the ratio of distributed income over the last 12 months to the fund's current Net Asset Value."},{"metadata":null,"text":"<strong>Product Structure:</strong> Indicates whether the fund buys the actual underlying securities in the index (i.e. Physical) or whether the fund gains exposure to those securities by buying derivatives, such as swaps (known as ’Synthetic’). Swaps are a form of contract that promises to provide the return of the security to the fund, but the fund does not hold the actual security. This can introduce a risk that the counterparty defaults on the “promise” or contract."},{"metadata":null,"text":"<strong>Methodology:</strong> Indicates whether the product is holding all index securities in the same weight as the index (replicating) or whether an optimised subset of index securities is used (optimised/sampled) in order to efficiently track index performance."}],"glossary.dailyliquidity":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<strong>Daily Maturing Asset: </strong>Are presented as a percentage of the fund’s total assets on the date stated"}],"glossary.weeklyliquidity":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<strong>Weekly Maturing Asset:</strong> The average of the weekly determinations of the difference between the total assets of the Fund attributable to an Allocated Sleeve and the total liabilities of the Fund attributable to such Allocated Sleeve, determined at the close of the last business day of each week."}],"holdings.all.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Exchange-traded index futures may be used to offset cash and receivables for the purpose of tracking the benchmark index."}],"holdings.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Holdings are subject to change."},{"metadata":null,"text":"<p class=\"disclaimer\"><br />The values shown for “market value,” “weight,” and “notional value” (the “calculated values”) are based off of a price provided by a third-party pricing vendor for the portfolio holding and do not reflect the impact of systematic fair valuation (“the vendor price”). The vendor price is not necessarily the price at which the Fund values the portfolio holding for the purposes of determining its net asset value (the “valuation price”). Holdings data shown reflects the investment book of record, which may differ from the accounting book of record used for the purposes of determining the Net Assets of the Fund. Notional value represents the portfolio's exposures based on the economic value of investments and options are delta-adjusted. Additionally, where applicable, foreign currency exchange rates with respect to the portfolio holdings denominated in non-U.S. currencies for the valuation price will be generally determined as of the close of business on the New York Stock Exchange, whereas for the vendor price will be generally determined as of 4 p.m. London. The calculated values may have been different if the valuation price were to have been used to calculate such values. The vendor price is as of the most recent date for which a price is available and may not necessarily be as of the date shown above.<br /><br />Please see the “Determination of Net Asset Value” section of each Fund’s prospectus for additional information on the Fund’s valuation policies and procedures.<br /><br />“Quantity” represents the number of shares, units or contracts of the corresponding security, as applicable per security type.</p>"}],"holdings.sec-lending.content":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<p>Securities lending is an established and well regulated activity in the investment management industry. It involves the transfer of securities (such as shares or bonds) from a Lender (in this case, the iShares fund) to a third-party (the Borrower). The Borrower will give the Lender collateral (the Borrower’s pledge) in the form of shares, bonds or cash, and will also pay the Lender a fee. This fee provides additional income for the fund and thus can help to reduce the total cost of ownership of an ETF.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>At BlackRock, securities lending is a core investment management function with dedicated trading, research and technology capabilities. The lending programme is designed to deliver superior absolute returns to clients, whilst maintaining a low risk profile. Funds participating in securities lending retain 62.5% of the income, while BlackRock receives 37.5% of the income and covers all the operational costs resulting from securities lending transactions.<br /><br /></p>"}],"holdings.sec-lending.content-table":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<div class=\"collateral-matrix\">\n      <p class=\"main-disclaimer oneds-body-m no-top-margin\">\n        The below table shows the Loan/Collateral Combinations and Collateral\n        Levels for our European Lending funds.\n      </p>\n\n      <div class=\"table-wrapper\">\n        <table class=\"collateral-table oneds-body-m-compact\">\n          <colgroup>\n            <col />\n            <col />\n            <col />\n            <col />\n            <col />\n          </colgroup>\n          <thead>\n            <tr class=\"table-title-row\">\n              <th></th>\n              <th></th>\n              <th class=\"table-title oneds-body-s-compact-bold\" colspan=\"3\">\n                COLLATERAL TYPES\n              </th>\n            </tr>\n            <tr class=\"columns oneds-body-s-compact\">\n              <th></th>\n              <th></th>\n              <th>Equities</th>\n              <th>Government, Supranational and Agency Bonds</th>\n              <th>Cash (Not for Reinvestment)</th>\n            </tr>\n          </thead>\n          <tbody>\n            <tr>\n              <td class=\"loan-types-col oneds-body-s-compact-bold\" rowspan=\"3\">\n                LOAN TYPES\n              </td>\n              <td class=\"row-title oneds-body-s-compact\">Equities</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">105% - 112%</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">105% - 106%</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">105% - 108%</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td class=\"row-title oneds-body-s-compact\">Government Bonds</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">110% - 112%</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">102.5% - 106%</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">102.5% - 105%</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td class=\"row-title oneds-body-s-compact\">Corporate Bonds</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">110% - 112%</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">104% - 106%</td>\n              <td class=\"value-cell\">103.5% - 105%</td>\n            </tr>\n          </tbody>\n        </table>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"main-disclaimer oneds-body-m\">\n        <p>\n          We also accept selected physically replicating Equity, Government\n          Bond, Credit and Commodity ETFs as collateral.\n        </p>\n        <p>\n          Collateral parameters depend on the collateral and the loan\n          combination, and the over collateralisation level may range from\n          102.5% to 112%. In this context, “Over Collateralisation” means that\n          the aggregate market value of collateral taken will exceed the overall\n          on-loan value. Collateral parameters are reviewed on an ongoing bases\n          and are subject to change.\n        </p>\n        <p>\n          With securities lending there is a risk of loss should the borrower\n          default before the securities are returned, and due to market\n          movements, the value of collateral held has fallen and/or the value of\n          the securities on loan has risen.\n        </p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <style>\n      /* Container + table base */\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table {\n        border-collapse: collapse;\n        width: 100%;\n        margin: var(--oneds-space-fluid-m, 32px) auto;\n      }\n\n      /* Base cell styles */\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table th,\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table td {\n        padding: var(--oneds-space-fluid-xs, 16px);\n        text-align: center;\n      }\n\n      /* Column widths */\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table colgroup col:nth-child(1),\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table colgroup col:nth-child(2) {\n        width: 75px;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table colgroup col:nth-child(3) {\n        width: 220px;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table colgroup col:nth-child(4) {\n        width: 260px;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table colgroup col:nth-child(5) {\n        width: 220px;\n      }\n\n      /* Row/column specific cells */\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table td.loan-types-col {\n        border-right: 1px solid #ccc;\n        vertical-align: middle;\n        text-align: center;\n        padding-left: 0;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table td.row-title {\n        text-align: right;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table td.value-cell {\n        border: 1px solid #ccc;\n      }\n\n      /* First row top border; left thick border after row-title */\n      .collateral-matrix\n        table.collateral-table\n        tbody\n        tr:first-child\n        td.value-cell {\n        border-top: 4px solid #000;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix\n        table.collateral-table\n        tbody\n        tr\n        td.row-title\n        + td.value-cell {\n        border-left: 4px solid #000;\n      }\n\n      /* Mobile adjustments */\n      @media (max-width: 768px) {\n        .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table td.loan-types-col {\n          writing-mode: vertical-lr;\n          text-orientation: mixed;\n          white-space: nowrap;\n          transform: rotate(180deg);\n          transform-origin: center;\n          padding-left: 12px;\n          padding-right: 0;\n        }\n\n        .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table th,\n        .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table td {\n          padding: var(--oneds-space-fluid-xs, 16px);\n        }\n\n        .collateral-matrix table.collateral-table td.value-cell {\n          padding: 8px;\n          min-width: 132px;\n          min-height: 44px;\n          white-space: nowrap;\n          vertical-align: middle;\n        }\n      }\n\n      /* Title underline */\n      .collateral-matrix .table-title {\n        border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;\n      }\n\n      /* Column header styling */\n      .collateral-matrix .columns th {\n        font-weight: normal;\n        vertical-align: bottom;\n      }\n\n      /* Disclaimer */\n      .collateral-matrix .main-disclaimer p {\n        margin-bottom: var(--oneds-space-fluid-s, 24px);\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix .main-disclaimer.no-top-margin {\n        margin-top: 0;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix\n        .main-disclaimer[data-disclaimer-fragment=\"holdings.sec-lending.content-table\"] {\n        margin-top: 0;\n        max-width: 100%;\n      }\n\n      .collateral-matrix .table-wrapper {\n        overflow-x: auto;\n        width: 100%;\n      }\n    </style>"}],"holdings.sec-lending.disclaimer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"The information in the Collateral Holdings table relates to securities obtained in the collateral basket under the securities lending programme for the fund in question. The information contained in this material is derived from proprietary and non-proprietary sources deemed by BlackRock to be reliable, is not necessarily all inclusive and is not guaranteed as to accuracy. Reliance upon information in this material is at the sole discretion of the reader. The primary risk in securities lending is that a borrower will default on their commitment to return lent securities while the value of the liquidated collateral does not exceed the cost of repurchasing the securities and the fund suffers a loss in respect of the short-fall.<br /><strong>~The information in the Lending Summary table will not be displayed for the funds that have participated in securities lending for less than 12 months.<br /></strong><br />*Annualised Securities Lending Return is calculated using unaudited 12 month net securities lending revenues to the fund divided by the average NAV of the fund over the same period. 62.5% of all securities lending income is paid directly into the fund, with BlackRock receiving 37.5% compensation which covers all operational costs. BlackRock’s policy is to disclose performance information quarterly subject to a one-month delay. This means that returns from 0/01/2015 to 31/12/2015 can be publicly disclosed from 01/02/2016.<br /><br />+Maximum on-loan figure may increase or decrease over time.<br /> **Collateral parameters depend on the collateral and the loan combination, and the over collateralisation level may range from 102.5% to 112%. In this context, “Over Collateralisation” means that the aggregate market value of collateral taken will exceed the overall on-loan value. Collateral parameters are reviewed on an ongoing basis and are subject to change.<br /> <!--<br /><br />Equities up to 50% of their ADTV (Average Daily Traded Volume) per borrower from the following indices are acceptable: FTSE All Share; Russell 1000; CAC AllShares; FTSE MIB; Netherlands AEX; SPI Swiss Performance; Topix; OMX; CDAX; Russell 2000; TSX; ASX 50; OMX Copenhagen 20; The Madrid Stock Exchange General Index (IGBM); HEX 25; PSI20; BEL 20; OBX; ATX; The Bank of New York ADR Index®<br /><br />Government bonds from the following countries are acceptable: UK; USA; Germany; France; Belgium; Netherlands; Switzerland; Canada; Sweden; Austria; Japan; Denmark; Finland; Australia; Norway; KfW (Kreditanstalt fuer Wiederaufbau). Issue limits apply.<br /><br />For operational reasons, cash collateral (in USD, EUR, or GBP) might be accepted, however not for reinvestment purposes. This happens infrequently and the collateral is held in a segregated tri-party account on behalf of the Trustee / Funds, where it is marked to market daily. <br /><br />These collateral parameters are reviewed on an ongoing basis and are subject to change.<br />-->"}],"how-to-buy.contact-advisor-content":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<div>\n\t\t\t\t<p class=\"col-heading\">Contact your advisor</p>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-details\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Contact a financial professional to discuss how iShares ETFs and ETPs can fit in your investment portfolio.</p>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t<button  id=\"sendEmailButton\" title=\"Email your advisor\" data-link-event=  \"fund header | how to buy | modal | email | email your advisor\"\n\t\t\t\t\tdata-track-event=\"event43\" class=\"button-cta\">\n\t\t\t\tEmail your advisor\n\t\t\t</button>"}],"how-to-buy.description":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<p>There are many ways to access iShares ETFs. Learn how you can add them to your portfolio.</p>"}],"how-to-buy.footer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<span class=\"em\"> Carefully consider the Funds' investment objectives, risk factors, and charges and expenses before investing. This and other information can be found in the Funds' prospectuses or, if available, the summary prospectuses, which may be obtained by visiting the iShares ETF and BlackRock Fund prospectus pages. Read the prospectus carefully before investing. Investing involves risk, including possible loss of principal. </span> <br /><br />Any links to third-party websites are provided for use at your own discretion. Each third party is solely responsible for the content presented and availability of its website. BlackRock does not control, monitor or maintain third-party websites, their content or the products/services they offer. Content may change without notice. When you leave BlackRock’s website and enter a third-party website, you will be subject to that site’s terms, policies and/or notices, including those related to privacy and security, as applicable. Please review those policies and notices on the third-party website. <br /><br />Before engaging Fidelity or any broker-dealer, you should evaluate the overall fees and charges of the firm as well as the services provided. Free commission offer applies to online purchases of select iShares ETFs in a Fidelity account. The sale of ETFs is subject to an activity assessment fee (from $0.01 to $0.03 per $1,000 of principal). For iShares ETFs, Fidelity receives compensation from the ETF sponsor and/or its affiliates in connection with an exclusive long-term marketing program that includes promotion of iShares ETFs and inclusion of iShares funds in certain Fidelity Brokerage Services platforms and investment programs. Please note, this security will not be marginable for 30 days from the settlement date, at which time it will automatically become eligible for margin collateral. Additional information about the sources, amounts, and terms of compensation can be found in the ETF’s prospectus and related documents. Fidelity may add or waive commissions on ETFs without prior notice. <br /><br />The Funds are distributed by BlackRock Investments, LLC (together with its affiliates, “BlackRock”). <br /><br />©2026 BlackRock, Inc or its affiliates. All Rights Reserved. <strong> BLACKROCK, iSHARES, iBONDS, LIFEPATH, ALADDIN</strong> and the iShares Core Graphic are trademarks of BlackRock, Inc. or its affiliates. All other trademarks are those of their respective owners. <br /><br /><span data-teams=\"true\">iCRMH1124U/S-3985892</span>"}],"how-to-buy.link-content":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<style type=\"text/css\" scoped=\"\">\n.modal-content .vi16.paragraph {padding-bottom:0; height: 50vh; overflow: auto;}\n.modal-content .vi16.paragraph p, .modal-content .vi16.tinymce ul, .modal-content .tinymce.vi16 .footnotes {width:auto;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content {display:table; margin:20px 0;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-left, .modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-right {width:50%; display:table-cell;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-left {border-right:1px solid #333; padding:0 20px 20px 0;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-right {padding:20px;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-heading {font-size:18px; font-weight:bold; text-align:center; margin-bottom:20px; padding-top:0;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-details {min-height:140px;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .button-cta {display:table; font:16px/22px 'FortExtraBold',Arial,sans-serif; background-color:#ffce00; color:#000; text-decoration:none; text-align:center; cursor:pointer; border-radius:2px; padding:11px 40px; margin:0 auto;}\n/* .modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .button-cta:hover {cursor:pointer;} */\n.modal-content .vi16.tinymce .footnotes .em {font-size:16px; font-weight:bold; color:#000;}\n/* MOBILE */\n@media only screen and (max-width:767px)\n{\n.modal-content .vi16.paragraph {height:auto;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content {margin:20px auto 0;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-left, .modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-right {width:100%; max-width:100%; display:block; border-right:0 none; border-bottom:1px solid #333; margin-bottom:20px; padding-right:0; padding-left:0;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-heading {margin-bottom:10px;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-details {min-height:0; margin-bottom:30px;}\n.modal-content .vi16 .buynow-content .col-details p {text-align:center;}\n}\n</style>\n<div class=\"vi16 tinymce paragraph\">\n<div class=\"buynow-content\">\n<div class=\"col-left\">\n<p class=\"col-heading\">Contact your advisor​</p>\n<div class=\"col-details\">\n<p>Contact a financial professional to discuss how iShares ETFs and ETPs can fit in your investment portfolio​.</p>\n</div>\n<button id=\"sendEmailButton\" title=\"Email your advisor​\" data-link-event=\"buy now: modal: button: email advisor\" data-track-event=\"event43\" class=\"button-cta\">Email your advisor​</button>\n<script>\n//<![CDATA[\ndocument.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {\n  document.getElementById(\"sendEmailButton\").addEventListener('click', sendEmail);\n  document.getElementById(\"sendEmailButton\").addEventListener('keydown', checkKeydown);\n});\nfunction checkKeydown(e) {\nif (e.key === 'Enter') sendEmail();\n}\nfunction sendEmail() {\nwindow.location.href = ('mailto:%20?Subject=Let’s%20discuss%20my%20portfolio&body=Please%20contact%20me%20to%20discuss%20my%20portfolio%20and%20this%20fund.%20Here%20is%20the%20URL: '+location.href.split(/\\?|#/)[0]);\n}\n//]]>\n</script>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-right\">\n<p class=\"col-heading\">Buy through your brokerage</p>\n<div class=\"col-details\">\n<p>iShares funds are available through online brokerage firms.<br /><br />All iShares ETFs and ETPs trade commission free online through Fidelity.<br /><br />By clicking on the button below, you will leave BlackRock’s website.</p>\n</div>\n<br />\n<a title=\"Visit Fidelity\" data-link-event=\"buy now: modal: button: visit fidelity\" data-track-event=\"event42\" href=\"https://www.fidelity.com/etfs/ishares-etf?ccsource=af_ishares_brh2b_product\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"button-cta\">Buy now on Fidelity</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"footnotes\">\n<span class=\"em\">Carefully consider the Funds' investment objectives, risk factors, and charges and expenses before investing. This and other information can be found in the Funds' prospectuses or, if available, the summary prospectuses, which may be obtained by visiting the iShares ETF and BlackRock Fund prospectus pages. Read the prospectus carefully before investing. Investing involves risk, including possible loss of principal.</span>\n<br /><br />\nAny links to third-party websites are provided for use at your own discretion. Each third party is solely responsible for the content presented and availability of its website. BlackRock does not control, monitor or maintain third-party websites, their content or the products/services they offer. Content may change without notice. When you leave BlackRock’s website and enter a third-party website, you will be subject to that site’s terms, policies and/or notices, including those related to privacy and security, as applicable. Please review those policies and notices on the third-party website.\n<br /><br />\nBefore engaging Fidelity or any broker-dealer, you should evaluate the overall fees and charges of the firm as well as the services provided. Free commission offer applies to online purchases of select iShares ETFs in a Fidelity account. The sale of ETFs is subject to an activity assessment fee (from $0.01 to $0.03 per $1,000 of principal). For iShares ETFs, Fidelity receives compensation from the ETF sponsor and/or its affiliates in connection with an exclusive long-term marketing program that includes promotion of iShares ETFs and inclusion of iShares funds in certain Fidelity Brokerage Services platforms and investment programs. Please note, this security will not be marginable for 30 days from the settlement date, at which time it will automatically become eligible for margin collateral. Additional information about the sources, amounts, and terms of compensation can be found in the ETF’s prospectus and related documents. Fidelity may add or waive commissions on ETFs without prior notice.\n<br /><br />\nThe Funds are distributed by BlackRock Investments, LLC (together with its affiliates, “BlackRock”).\n<br /><br />\n©2024 BlackRock, Inc or its affiliates. All Rights Reserved. <strong> BLACKROCK, iSHARES, iBONDS, LIFEPATH, ALADDIN</strong> and the iShares Core Graphic are trademarks of BlackRock, Inc. or its affiliates. All other trademarks are those of their respective owners.\n\n<br /><br />\niCRMH0924U/S-3874576</p>\n</div>"}],"how-to-buy.title":[{"metadata":null,"text":"READY TO INVEST?"}],"important.information":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<p><span class=\"emphasis\">Important Information: Capital at Risk.</span> The value of investments and the income from them can fall as well as rise and are not guaranteed. Investors may not get back the amount originally invested.</p>"}],"index_overview.index_overview":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Index Overview"}],"key_benefits":[{"metadata":null,"text":"<p>1. Exposure to small public U.S. companies</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>2. Access to 2000 small-cap domestic stocks in a single fund</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>3. Use to diversify a U.S. stock allocation and seek long-term growth in your portfolio</p>"}],"kiid-exchange-traded-fund.header":[{"metadata":null,"text":"fred.investorClassCode USD fred.useOfProfit"}],"kiid-fund-isin.label":[{"metadata":null,"text":"ISIN :"}],"kiid-performance-historic-performance.text":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Historic performance to 31 December 2025"}],"kiid-risk-non-srri-main.text-new":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Particular risks not adequately captured by the risk indicator include:"}],"kiid-share-class-name.header":[{"metadata":null,"text":"fred.investorClassCode USD fred.useOfProfit"}],"label.10k_growth_chart.beginning_value":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Beginning Value"}],"label.10k_growth_chart.date":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Date"}],"label.10k_growth_chart.ending_value":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Ending Value"}],"label.10kgrowthchart.growth":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Growth"}],"label.30daysecyield":[{"metadata":null,"text":"30 Day SEC Yield"}],"label.achieved-tracking-error":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Achieved Tracking-<br />Error % (3 Year)"}],"label.as_of":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Fact Sheet as of"}],"label.average_market_capitalization":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Average Market Capitalization"}],"label.calendar_year":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Calendar Year"}],"label.country_breakdown.other_includes":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Other Includes"}],"label.dealinginformation.dealingdeadline":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Trading Deadline"}],"label.distributions.dividend":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Total Distribution"}],"label.documentdate":[{"metadata":null,"text":"All other data as at"}],"label.exchange.bloombergcode":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Bloomberg Ticker"}],"label.exchange.exchangename":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Exchange"}],"label.exchange.other_exchange":[{"metadata":null,"text":"This product is also listed on:"}],"label.exchange.reuterscode":[{"metadata":null,"text":"RIC"}],"label.exchange.sedol":[{"metadata":null,"text":"SEDOL"}],"label.exchange.ticker":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Ticker"}],"label.exchange.tradingcurrency":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Trading Currency"}],"label.exchange.valoren":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Valor"}],"label.exchange.wkn":[{"metadata":null,"text":"WKN"}],"label.factsheet":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Factsheet"}],"label.feedata.acquiredfundfeesandexpenses":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Acquired Fund Fees and Expenses"}],"label.feedata.annualmgtcharges":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Annual Management Fee"}],"label.feedata.expenseratio":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Expense Ratio"}],"label.feedata.feewaiver":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Fee Waivers"}],"label.feedata.foreigntaxesandotherexpenses":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Foreign Taxes and Other Expenses"}],"label.feedata.forwardfee":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Forward Structure Costs"}],"label.feedata.forwardfee.to":[{"metadata":null,"text":"to"}],"label.feedata.managementexpenseratiomer":[{"metadata":null,"text":"Management Expense Ratio (MER)"}],"label.feedata.